Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.57,0:02:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.42,0:15:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!

Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.08,0:01:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,, Welcome. I am the second Rare Hunter, Pandora.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.20,0:01:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also known as the Conjurer, and user of the {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.47,0:01:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,User of the {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.62,0:01:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.25,0:01:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a 100-tooth carbide tipped saw you see in magic shows!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.72,0:01:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand the rules of this duel yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.25,0:01:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this {\i1}fun{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A battle with people's {\i1}lives{\i0} on the line...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking you if you think it's {\i1}fun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.57,0:01:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Because {\i1}I{\i0} will be the winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.79,0:02:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You filthy {\i1}scum{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.09,0:02:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll show you what a true duelist's fight looks like!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.39,0:02:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Black Magic From the Soul"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.75,0:02:18.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}! Direct Attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.10,0:02:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pandora, if you cut your cards like that, you're just using them for your own needs!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.66,0:02:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you continue the game like this, you'll feel the full anger of those cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.29,0:02:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give this game up right now to save yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.67,0:02:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Give up"? Who will?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is great! The best!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.47,0:02:56.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Yugi... I am a conjurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.93,0:03:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you are merely the audience for my show.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the show {\i1}I{\i0} control.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.81,0:03:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wouldn't be a {\b0}real{\b1} magician if I didn't have some tricks up my sleeve...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:13.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be this game's victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.04,0:03:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning I will be the one to escape and {\i1}survive{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.99,0:03:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one who'll be chopped to mincemeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.09,0:03:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is {\i1}you{\i0}, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.09,0:03:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only a fool {\i1}blinded{\i0} by his own greed would say such words...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.58,0:03:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's continue the game, Pandora!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.85,0:03:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just where did Yugi disappear to?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Jounouchi predicted, he must have been captured by the Ghouls.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.19,0:03:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to hurry and fine him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.82,0:03:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he could be anywhere. Where should we start looking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.13,0:03:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let's resume the duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi only has {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't allow him to direct attack me next turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.73,0:04:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H2040A9&}Killer Tomato{\r} in Defense Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, I place a card face-down on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.64,0:04:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.81,0:04:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He only has a monster in Defense Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.46,0:04:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can Summon another monster on my turn, I can finish this match.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.90,0:04:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi will surely Summon a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that moment, my {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} shall revive!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.69,0:04:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon {\c&H3896AE&}Magnet Warrior Beta{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.32,0:04:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.50,0:04:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.21,0:04:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! A trap?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.74,0:04:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H911ADE&}Reviving Coffin of Black Magic{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.44,0:04:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It offers a Summoned monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.93,0:04:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H911ADE&}Reviving Coffin of Black Magic{\r} takes the soul of an enemy's monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.50,0:05:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as one of my own monster's soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.27,0:05:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It then revives the {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}'s soul residing in my Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.84,0:05:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive your {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.04,0:05:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.15,0:05:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's two {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}s on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.32,0:05:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the true battle begins, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.68,0:05:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters with the same Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.92,0:05:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither can directly attack each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.64,0:05:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, we'll both have to use our Magic and Trap Cards
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.84,0:05:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to try and defeat our {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}s.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.73,0:05:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's become a battle of wits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.49,0:05:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this turn, I'll place 2 set cards face-down on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.19,0:06:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you're up to, Yugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.61,0:06:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever uses their {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} to the fullest...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.91,0:06:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's now my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.73,0:06:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I play 2 set cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.46,0:06:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.81,0:06:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place two cards face-down. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.62,0:06:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.47,0:06:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another set card face-down. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My{\i0} turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My{\i0} turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.70,0:06:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we both have 5 cards face-down on the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.52,0:06:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll take the first strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.76,0:06:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Mystic Guillotine{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.41,0:06:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! A guillotine?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.90,0:07:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.79,0:07:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi! This is the end of your {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Magic Card open!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.61,0:07:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Magical Silk Hats{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.61,0:07:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magical Hats
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.48,0:07:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Magical Silk Hats{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.53,0:07:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll open my second face-down card! {\c&H36A637&}Thousand Knives{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:37.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.39,0:07:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw through it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.12,0:07:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, {\c&H36A637&}Magic Removal{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.86,0:07:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you...! I was so close, too...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.06,0:07:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.45,0:08:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}s have been demolished!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.93,0:08:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Resurrection of the Dead{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.83,0:08:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Resurrection of the Dead{\r}...! So this was also his hidden trump card?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.84,0:08:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've fought against my {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I praise you, Pandora.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.81,0:08:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.52,0:08:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.75,0:08:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pandora, your skills are quite good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a duelist of this caliber, you shouldn't have fallen to this level so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.42,0:08:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it you fall so low as to follow Malik, and act as one of Ghoul's Rare Hunters?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.76,0:08:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this face.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.81,0:08:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up till now, I've been a professional magician for a number of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.96,0:09:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was known around the world, and had built the steady living I yearned for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, above all, I met my love, Catherine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.08,0:09:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, after a failed escape trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.15,0:09:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My life as a famous magician as well as Catherine's love for me was taken from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.80,0:09:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I focused on myself, and rejected Catherine's love for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.14,0:09:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her heart disappeared, as if by magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.33,0:09:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally came to realize how important Catherine's love for me was afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.56,0:10:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, it was already too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I had given up all hope, that man appeared before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he promised me that if I would kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.44,0:10:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With his Millennium Rod's power, he would recover Catherine's love for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.68,0:10:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you encourage your lover to trust and believe in you? Even now, it isn't too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.49,0:10:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honor your girlfriend with your heart and soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.32,0:10:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a kid after all, aren't you. Your opinion is quite extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.30,0:10:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trust isn't possible in anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.72,0:10:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to Malik, Catherine will return to my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.11,0:10:51.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catherine is already waiting for me over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.32,0:10:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us return to France and start over!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.45,0:10:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Malik controlling her mind as well...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.88,0:11:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catherine, just let me get rid of Yugi. Then we can be together!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.33,0:11:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for that... I will end your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.35,0:11:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like in a Duel, you have to trust one another!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.34,0:11:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens, I believe in my {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.76,0:11:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this duel, whoever trusts in his own cards will determine the outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.68,0:11:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the key to victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.49,0:11:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, you're more naive than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.05,0:11:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.89,0:11:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As expected. You're no doubt qualified to be called a {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} user.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.12,0:11:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Although...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.06,0:11:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You didn't forget, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Before this duel even started,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.18,0:11:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I told you I was the {\i0}real{\i1} {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} user.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In other words, I've made the preparations to control the magician in my deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.01,0:11:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And even more, it's flawless!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.60,0:12:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi... where'd you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.40,0:12:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The new Duel Disk System should connect with Kaiba Corporation's main computer all at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, because the search can't be completed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.84,0:12:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if Yugi ended up in a duel against the Ghouls...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.92,0:12:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's most likely a false duel system.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.98,0:13:03.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Search the entire Domino City for any unknown Duel Ring being accessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.46,0:13:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.04,0:13:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figure that a basement or something is blocking the transmission from reaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.53,0:13:11.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so there's a chance it's somewhere close.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.82,0:13:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother, I'll go check it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.64,0:13:34.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.99,0:13:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a card face-down on the field and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.60,0:13:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:46.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I place 2 set cards face-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.94,0:13:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming! Magic Card, {\c&H36A637&}Beckon to Dark{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.68,0:14:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! That is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.91,0:14:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card {\c&H36A637&}Beckon to Dark{\r} will snatch one of the opponent's monsters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.76,0:14:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and drag them into the depths of darkness with a demon's claw.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.56,0:14:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm referring to your {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.41,0:14:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'll let you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.87,0:14:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap Card! {\c&H911ADE&}Hand Mirror of Spirit{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this Trap Card, I'll control your Magic Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.57,0:14:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.57,0:14:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an3}What?!
Dialogue: 1,0:14:34.46,0:14:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That hand was merely a decoy to lure you into playing your Trap Card.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.14,0:14:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My aim was this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.75,0:14:48.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a Trap Card that activates in response to another Trap Card!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.09,0:14:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H911ADE&}Nightmare Cross{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.93,0:15:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now your {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} can only wait on the side lines
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as your death is acted out in front of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.02,0:15:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} is taken out of commission, the enemy can easily diminish my Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you prepared yourself well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.04,0:15:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, my servant! {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.68,0:15:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.48,0:15:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about that same Black Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.50,0:15:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now~! Showtime~!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.09,0:15:54.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Saw-Blade Cutter will now assault the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.64,0:16:04.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now my magic show has finally reached its climax.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.62,0:16:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment your Life reaches 0, my task will be complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as you are met with despair, the show's curtain will drop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.04,0:16:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, it's your last turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.68,0:16:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we just continue to randomly search the city like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.49,0:16:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the kidnappers may do unspeakable things!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.59,0:16:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if this keeps up, Yugi will...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.18,0:16:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Isn't that Mokuba-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.52,0:16:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba, it's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.09,0:16:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi has... Yugi has been taken somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.43,0:16:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like he's been captured by someone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.03,0:17:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know the location.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.61,0:17:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to head there right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.80,0:17:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.79,0:17:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.75,0:17:07.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.29,0:17:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon {\c&H2040A9&}Big Shield Gardna{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.38,0:17:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.60,0:17:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This turn, I have nothing to stop this guy with.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.23,0:17:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You put out a wall monster, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.28,0:17:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You're thinking as long as you have a wall monster, I can't do anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.12,0:17:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's all in vein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, your life will end this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.49,0:17:36.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you're prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.29,0:17:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you prepared yourself well?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.41,0:17:42.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.03,0:17:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the time being, I Summon 1 monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.65,0:17:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H25C0E7&}Killer Doll{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.78,0:17:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Magic Card that will cause your death!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.62,0:17:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Field Magic, {\c&H36A637&}Ectoplasmer{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.75,0:18:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! That card...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.40,0:18:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, there's a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.69,0:18:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Magic Card transforms my monster into Ectoplasm energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.67,0:18:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I can then directly attack the player.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.50,0:18:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will pass right through all wall monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be...! You're willing to sacrifice your own monster's soul?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.91,0:18:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.35,0:18:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The selected monster will die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.89,0:18:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's to win this match and get back Catherine,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my monster's soul is nothing but a stepping stone to get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catherine, just a while longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.26,0:18:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a while longer, and you'll be able to come out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.09,0:18:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait a little longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.96,0:18:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.94,0:18:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this turn, I shall turn both {\c&H25C0E7&}Killer Doll{\r} and {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} into Ectoplasm!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.00,0:18:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Ectoplasmer{\r}, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.31,0:18:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.94,0:19:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a bit more and I'm done for...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.81,0:19:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, as a {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} user, do you understand the reason I am unbeatable?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.51,0:19:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.17,0:19:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because I can step on my servants with no second thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.98,0:19:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it means their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.93,0:19:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The way you try to win is pure naivety.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.47,0:19:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See there, your servant is unable to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't protect you or do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.85,0:19:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it okay to use the life of your servants to defeat the enemy laid out in front of you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.10,0:19:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.71,0:19:54.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} devotes its life and soul to my needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.31,0:19:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For my victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:19:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's finally the finale.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.81,0:20:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H36A637&}Ectoplasmer{\r}, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.70,0:20:05.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} into Ectoplasm!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.11,0:20:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pandora, your monster is crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.08,0:20:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's of no matter! {\c&H36A637&}Ectoplasmer{\r}, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.33,0:20:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.80,0:20:31.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Th-That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.89,0:20:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.50,0:20:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}, in order to stop it, transformed itself into Ectoplasm as well!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.58,0:20:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}... You... For my sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.02,0:21:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This turn, because I turned my monster into Ectoplasm, {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} was destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.16,0:21:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, his {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} was also affected at the same time...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.66,0:21:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But a mere card chose to extract itself by {\c&H36A637&}Ectoplasmer{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.94,0:21:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and protect the player from certain death...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.49,0:21:22.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tyranny isn't the only method to win a game!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.24,0:21:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teach you this, Pandora!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.54,0:21:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}'s sacrifice, Yugi was able to escape a great pinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.79,0:21:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the next time Pandora launches an attack, it's all over!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.93,0:21:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pandora proceeds to Summon his second {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.78,0:21:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's another type of {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r} still hiding in Yugi's deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.35,0:21:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? There's a disciple of {\c&H3896AE&}Black Magician{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.43,0:22:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time! "Magician's Disciple: Black Magician Girl"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.51,0:22:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.79,0:22:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I feel like I've been here, been in this place before
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.22,0:22:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With the classroom shaded by the setting sun
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.64,0:22:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I laughed along and pointed with my too shortly cut bangs
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Little by little, time keeps going
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.04,0:23:01.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My bangs now over my eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.21,0:23:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The sunset took everyone together
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.42,0:23:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure nothing changed while we were there
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.68,0:23:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.85,0:23:22.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I kept on searching for something
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.02,0:23:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you understood such a senseless time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.19,0:23:29.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.91,0:23:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From here, always...
